# Backend Python Conventions

## Project layout

```
backend/
  app/
    main.py          — FastAPI app, CORS, router mounts
    models/schemas.py — all Pydantic request/response models
    routers/          — thin route handlers (upload, audit, analyze)
    services/         — business logic (pdf_parser, vector_store, gemini)
  scripts/            — CLI tools (ingest_policies)
```

## Patterns to follow

- Route handlers validate input via Pydantic models and delegate to services
- Services are importable functions/classes, not router-aware
- Use `async def` for route handlers; blocking I/O (pdfplumber, chromadb) runs in the default thread pool via `asyncio.to_thread` or is acceptable in the current single-worker setup
- SSE responses use `StreamingResponse(media_type="text/event-stream")` with `data: {json}\n\n` format
- Error responses: raise `HTTPException` with meaningful status codes (400 bad request, 422 parse failure, 500 service error)

## Gemini integration

- Batch size is 5 questions per Gemini call — adjustable but keep batching to avoid rate limits
- System prompt requires structured JSON array output — always validate/coerce the response
- Missing questions in Gemini's response should be backfilled as `not_met` with an error evidence string

## Vector store

- Collection name: `policies`
- Embedding model: `gemini-embedding-001` via custom `GoogleEmbeddingFunction`
- Chunk metadata must include: `policy_id`, `title`, `section`, `source_file`
- Dedup retrieved chunks by text content before sending to Gemini
